.TH "SOURCEBUFFER.UPDATESTART_EVENT" "3JS" "September 29, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
SourceBuffer.updatestart_event \- SourceBuffer: updatestart event
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Dedicated Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]updatestart\f[B]\f[R] event of the
\f[CR]SourceBuffer\f[R] interface signals the beginning of an
\f[CR]appendBuffer()\f[R] or \f[CR]remove()\f[R] operation.
The \f[CR]updating\f[R] attribute transitions from \f[CR]false\f[R] to
\f[CR]true\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqupdatestart\(dq, (event) => { })

onupdatestart = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Listening for the updatestart event
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] sourceBuffer = source.addSourceBuffer(mimeCodec);
sourceBuffer.addEventListener(\(dqupdatestart\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  downloadStatus.textContent = \(dqModifying buffer...\(dq;
});
sourceBuffer.addEventListener(\(dqupdateend\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  downloadStatus.textContent = \(dqModification complete\(dq;
});
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]SourceBuffer.appendBuffer()\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]SourceBuffer.remove()\f[R]
